About

TLDR (Because I don't care)

Use saito_ena <lora:saitoEna_v1:1> in positiv promt.

If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) ;D

About

Yuru Camp is one of my favourite anime, so I thought it would be only fair to create a LoRa for the main characters of the anime... But instead of using the anime series as a source for the training, I used the film, which takes place some years (I think its 3 years) after the anime series, so all the main characters are adults and look a bit different (oh really?) than in the series...

This LoRa is for Ena. I like her and Chikuwa is just cute, even though he is an old man now... What is a bit sad is the fact that she has the least screentime with her eyes open. (Often they are closed :<)

Have a look at the other character LoRa from the same film:

  • Kagamihara Nadeshiko

  • Inuyama Aoi

  • Shima Rin

  • Saito Ena

  • Ogaki Chiaki

Training

For Ena I collected 28 images from the movie.

To be hornest, in my opinon v1 is a total failure, the training data is simply to similar... I release v1 for now but will defenitily work on a v2 and try to improve

Usage

No weight adjustments required...

saito_ena <lora:saitoEna_v1:1>

items.name: Digimon Adventures Style LoRA
items.description:
Digimon Adventures style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

Trained on images from the 2020 Digimon Adventures anime. Digimons weren't tagged, so it can't reproduce specific ones, but you can make custom monsters with it pretty easily.

As always, this is a style LoRa, meaning it's not targeted at making characters from the show without a dedicated TI/LoRA. However, it can get pretty close with adequate prompting.

I tested it on AnyLoRA ckpt at weight 1 with trigger digimon.

The negative embedding I used is here: https://civitai.com/models/71961/fast-negative-embedding

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1)

The plot follows Mark (Scott), an employee of Lumon Industries who agrees to a "severance" program in which his non-work memories are separated from his work memories. Helly is the new employee. items.name: Masters of the Universe - He-Man
items.description:
BY THE POWER OF GRAYSKULL

I noticed a distinct lack of 80's characters on here and being a Gen-X'er, I had to rectify that issue. To continue the series, here is is - the Man, the Myth, the Unattainable Ideal of Masculinity - He-Man from Masters of the Universe. This Lora was trained on images from the 1980's Funimation cartoon and product images for 80's era toys. I did not use images from the live-action movie nor the new Netflix series. S

Image was trained on SD1.5, so it is good for most other checkpoints. The strength can vary from 0.5-1, but I would recommend setting the strength to 0.7-0.8. Highres.fx = VERY YES. I usually go about 1/2 of my initial steps with a denoising strength of 0.3-0.4. If you really want to hulk him out, I recommend using one of the various supermuscle LoRAs available.

Activation word is "he-man". Good luck, have fun, and stay tuned for more 80's icons!

items.description:
Ao Gennai || Frame Arms Girl

This LoRA should primarily resemble her from the anime, but wouldn't it be interesting to see how the anime design could translate to a figure? Hmmm. Used kohya_ss gui.

Here are some parameters and helpful keywords:

• Checkpoint: AbyssOrangeMix3

• Trigger Word: gennai ao

• Weight: 1 is best.

Keywords:

brown hair, pink shirt, open hoodie, yellow ribbon

( some different outfits: school uniform, plaid skirt, black hoodie )

A sample image included her wearing a frame arms styled battlesuit, adding battlesuit to prompt can yield stellar results!

To produce similar results I recommend EasyNegative, this negative embedding was used in the sample images. I'm also using Clip Skip 2 and hires fix.

items.name: Hydaelyn Final Fantasy XIV by Kangaxx
items.description:
So I brought mommy here on Civitai. This was my last Lora for Final Fantasy XIV, I need a change of scenery so I will switch to make Loras for other IPs for now.

This was trained on only 15 images, believe or not. There were no decent images of her at all. I had to really work hard to get high quality images using img2img and adjusting them in GIMP.

Same as on my other Loras, it's trained on Novel AI model (animefull-final-pruned), use models which are based on this for best results. Realistic models should work as well since she's not an anime character.

Use Clip Skip 2 when using the Lora.

For her default attire/look also include the following trigger words in addition to the main trigger word: veil, white bodysuit, white wings, cape, crown.

Optional trigger words: pale skin, lipstick.

If you feel that her wings, cape and veil are overcrowding the image, don't use them in the prompt.

Use the Lora at 0.7-0.9 weight for optimal results.

To remove her clothes/change her attire, you need to lower the weight to 0.5-0.6. Add white hair and blue eyes to guide the AI back to her design when lowering the weight.

Checkpoints used in the examples:

  • Corneo's 7th Heaven Mix

  • Anyhentai

  • AbyssOrangeMix2NSFW

  • MeinaHentai

  • Grapefruit

  • KotosMix

  • Hassaku

items.name: Walter Sobchak from "The Big Lebowski"
items.description:
Walter Sobchak is a memorable character from the movie "The Big Lebowski," directed by Joel and Ethan Coen. He is portrayed by John Goodman and is known for his strong personality and unwavering conviction in his beliefs.

Walter Sobchak is a Vietnam War veteran who is fiercely loyal to his friends and holds firm to his personal principles. He is often seen wearing his military-style clothing, which reflects his military background and his strict adherence to a code of conduct. Walter is portrayed as a brash and confrontational character, unafraid to speak his mind and stand up for what he believes is right.

One of Walter's defining traits is his strong sense of morality and justice, which he applies to every aspect of his life. He frequently engages in debates and arguments, passionately defending his viewpoints and criticizing those he disagrees with. Despite his gruff demeanor, Walter genuinely cares about the people around him, particularly his close friend, The Dude (played by Jeff Bridges), whom he fiercely protects.

If you want to change clothes, it is recommended to remove the tag lilith aensland first

如果你想换装，建议先去掉lilith aensland这个tag

————————————————————————————————————————

I would like to give you a suggestion. With the increase of lora models, many characters have multiple lora. Generally speaking, the file size of lora is determined by the dim parameter, such as 8M 18M 36M 72M 144M and so on. The larger the lora, the better the effect when switching to a large model, especially when an anime character is switched to a live model. According to my test, if you only make animation pictures, about 36M lora is enough, if you want to make real-life pictures, at least 72M lora should be used. Of course, the lora produced by some experts can appropriately relax this range.

给大家一个建议，随着lora模型变多，很多角色都有多个lora，通常来说，lora的文件大小由dim参数决定，比如8M 18M 36M 72M 144M等。体积越大的lora在切换大模型时效果越好，尤其是动漫人物切换到真人模型中使用。按照我的体感，如果你只制作动漫图片，36M左右的lora足够了，如果你想制作真人图片，至少要使用72M的lora，不然特征会丢失很多。当然，由一些大佬制作的lora可以适当放宽这个范围。比如上千张图片制作的10M大小的lora，动漫人物也会相当还原，但是通常情况下，如果你是跑真人图片，效果未必有3,40张图片制作的144M的Lora会更好。
